'''Antoine Alpha Mendy''' (born 27 May 2004) is a professional [[association football|football]]er who plays as a [[right-back]] and [[centre-back]] for {{French football updater|Nice}} club [[OGC Nice|Nice]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].

==Club career==
Mendy is a youth product of [[OGC Nice|Nice]] since the age of 10, and worked his way up their youth categories. He began his senior career with their reserves in 2021, and signed his first professional contract with the club on 29 September 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.maxifoot.fr/nice/antoine-mendy-passe-pro-officiel-foot-376531.htm|title=Nice : Antoine Mendy passe pro (officiel)|website=news.maxifoot.fr}}</ref>

He made his professional and [[Ligue 1]] with Nice as a late substitute in a 1–1 win over [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]] on 16 October 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.monacomatin.mc/football/accroche-a-auxerre-1-1-logc-nice-sinquiete-en-prime-pour-delort-801123|title=Accroché à Auxerre (1-1), l'OGC Nice s'inquiète en prime pour Delort|first=La|last=rédaction|date=16 October 2022|website=Monaco-Matin}}</ref>

In Oct 2025, he is listed as one of the ESPN soccer's next generation of entertainers.<ref>{{Cite web|title=The next generation of entertainers: 15 young stars lighting up Europe |url=https://www.espn.com.sg/soccer/story/_/id/46770791/the-next-gen-entertainers-15-young-stars-lighting-europe|date=30 October 2025|website=ESPN}}</ref>

==International career==
Antoine Mendy received his first call-up to the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]] in 22 March 2025 to take part in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccerway.com/matches/2025/03/22/-/-/-/-/4236795|title=Sudan vs. Senegal|date=22 March 2025|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

He made his debut as a starter in a goalless draw against [[Sudan national football team|Sudan]], then came on as a substitute against [[Togo national football team|Togo]], earning praise for his defensive solidity.<ref>{{cite web|date=27 March 2025 |title=Antoine Mendy, une première réussie en équipe nationale ! |url=https://wiwsport.com/2025/03/27/antoine-mendy-une-premiere-reussie-en-equipe-nationale/ |website=wiwsport.com}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

==Personal life==
Born in [[France]], Mendy is of [[Senegal]]ese descent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2022/10/01/nice-lucien-favre-elogieux-envers-antoine-mendy/|title=Nice : Lucien Favre élogieux envers Antoine Mendy|first=Alfred|last=ZIKPI|date=1 October 2022}}</ref>

